<p>Lafayette's Hot-Humid climate presents unique challenges that require carefully selected HVAC systems optimized for both temperature control and humidity management. The ideal HVAC system for Lafayette homes should feature a minimum SEER rating of 16-18, with higher ratings of 20+ providing better long-term savings given the extended cooling season that runs from April through October. Heat pumps are particularly effective in Lafayette's moderate winter climate, providing efficient heating when temperatures occasionally drop while delivering excellent cooling performance during the dominant warm months.</p>

<p>Variable-speed systems excel in Lafayette's climate by providing precise humidity control and consistent comfort while operating more efficiently than single-stage units. For the average 1,820 square foot Lafayette home, a properly sized 2.5 to 3-ton system typically provides adequate capacity. Dehumidification features are essential, as Lafayette's humidity levels often exceed 80% during summer months. Ductwork design and sealing become critical in the humid climate to prevent condensation issues and maintain efficiency. Smart thermostats paired with zoning systems can provide additional savings by optimizing comfort in occupied areas while reducing energy waste in unused spaces.</p>

