<p>Suburban neighborhoods like Broadmoor, Woodvale, and areas along Johnston Street offer excellent solar potential with spacious lots and fewer shading concerns. These areas, populated with homes from the 1970s-1990s, frequently benefit from both solar installations and HVAC upgrades as original systems reach replacement age. Newer developments in areas like Youngsville and Broussard (part of greater Lafayette) feature modern homes with energy-efficient construction that maximizes solar benefits and reduces overall HVAC loads. The proximity to University of Louisiana at Lafayette creates rental markets where energy efficiency improvements can provide attractive returns for property investors.</p>

